	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Tue, Dec 10th 12:51 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=141192><span id= >Kriil</span></a><br><span id=notbold>2 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>&nbsp;&nbsp; Using allakhazam's mana calculator on my characters I have input on the site, my level 46 cleric gets 4.6 mana per wisdom point from wis items(I did not include base mana in my calculations since that has a different ratio). So from 200 to 255 wisdom you get (55x4.6) 253 mana.  Therefore at my level (this wis/mana conversion ratio is supposed to change according to level) I would get 41.4 mana from the truewind earring.   Make sure you calculate the total mana an item gives before you consider buying it.</p>&nbsp;<br>Linea Lifebringer<br>Level 46 Cleric<br>Prexus</td></tr>
